casebody.data:
Conner v. Paxson and Others, in Error.

Stat. 1817, p. 293; — 1823, p. 209. — Ackler v. Oldham, 1 Marsh. Ky. R. 471.

HELD, that the record of an order of Court granting a right of ferry, need not show that the rates have been fixed by the Court, nor that the party has executed a bond, according to law (1).
